trans-unit.source: Encapsulates the value and location of a <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGrid"></xref> cell for use when copying content to the Clipboard.
This structure is used by the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.DataGridRowClipboardEventArgs.ClipboardRowContent%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> structure.
The data item for the row that contains the cell being copied.
The column that contains the cell being copied.
The text value of the cell being copied.
Gets the column that contains the cell being copied.
The column that contains the cell being copied.
Gets the text value of the cell being copied.
The text value of the cell being copied.
Indicates whether the current and specified <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> instances are equivalent.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> instance to compare with the current <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> instance.

`true` if the current and specified <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> instances have the same <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent.Item"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent.Column"></xref>, and <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent.Content"></xref> property values; otherwise, `false`.
Returns the hash code for this <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> instance.

The hash code is based on the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent.Item%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent.Column%2A>, and <xref:System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent.Content%2A> property values.
The hash code for this <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> instance.
Gets the data item for the row that contains the cell being copied.
The data item for the row that contains the cell being copied.
Indicates whether the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> instances are equivalent.
The first <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> instance to be compared.
The second <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> instance to be compared.

`true` if the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> instances have the same <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent.Item"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent.Column"></xref>, and <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent.Content"></xref> property values; otherwise, `false`.
Indicates whether the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> instances are not equivalent.
The first <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> instance to be compared.
The second <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> instance to be compared.

`true` if the current and specified <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent"></xref> instances do not have the same <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent.Item"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent.Column"></xref>, and <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.DataGridClipboardCellContent.Content"></xref> property values; otherwise, `false`.
